I was anxiously searching for a recipe for the Persian Lima Beans I had soaking one rainy Saturday afternoon, and found this one. It seemed like a very unlikely combination of ingredients, but I gave it a shot, and would have to say this is a winner. The only substitution I made was to use garlic in place of the scallions. It was much better the next day, and I definitely prefer it served warm. YUM!

